🔧 Best Practices

✔ Use `with open()` whenever possible
✔ Handle exceptions properly
✔ Close files after use
✔ Use meaningful file names
✔ Choose correct file mode

---

⚠️ Common Mistakes

❌ Forgetting to close files
❌ Using wrong file mode
❌ Overwriting files accidentally with `w`
❌ Not handling FileNotFoundError
❌ Reading huge files at once

---

🧠 Interview Answer (Simple)

> File handling in Python is used to read, write, append, and manage files. The `open()` function is used with different file modes like `r`, `w`, and `a`. The `with open()` statement is the recommended approach because it automatically closes files.

